item.description:
We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Scientist to join our dynamic team. As a Senior Data Scientist, you will play a pivotal role in driving data-driven decision-making across the organization. You will be responsible for leading advanced analytics projects, developing machine learning models, and providing strategic insights to optimize business processes and outcomes.

Responsibilities:

- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities and develop data-driven strategies.
- Design and implement machine learning models and algorithms to solve complex business problems.
- Perform exploratory data analysis to uncover insights and trends in large datasets.
- Develop predictive models for customer behavior, demand forecasting, and other business metrics.
- Evaluate model performance, conduct A/B testing, and iterate on models to improve accuracy and efficiency.
- Communicate findings and recommendations to senior management and stakeholders through clear visualizations and presentations.
- Stay updated with the latest advancements in data science and machine learning techniques.

Requirements:
- Master’s or Ph.D. in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or related field.
- Proven experience (5+ years) in a data scientist role, with a focus on machine learning, predictive modeling, and statistical analysis.
- Strong proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, with experience in libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or Scikit-Learn.
- Hands-on experience with SQL, NoSQL databases, and big data technologies (e.g., Hadoop, Spark).
- Solid understanding of data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) and techniques to present complex data insights.
- Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to translate business requirements into technical solutions.
- Strong communication skills and the ability to collaborate effectively with diverse teams.

item.title: Mathnasium Learning Centers - Senior Data Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
At Mathnasium, we make math make sense. With over 1,100 franchised learning centers worldwide, Mathnasium is a must-have resource for families who want to ensure their kids meet their full academic potential. The Business Intelligence team is responsible for developing systems, answering business problems, crafting insights, and delivering dashboards at scale to our 1,100 global franchisees in an easily consumable way. The BI team supports all business units including but not limited to education teams, field ops, finance, marketing, strategy, sales, and operations by taking a deep dive into data and evaluating performance, business impact, and recommending the best path forward.

What you’ll do:
• Develop and deliver scalable solutions, comprehensive reports, and actionable insights to advance business strategies.
• Translate sophisticated business questions into SQL including accurate cohorting, scaffolding, calculations, filtering criteria and/or aggregations, and more
• Pursue data quality, troubleshoot data anomalies, validate data accuracy, and drive issues to resolution
• Design, develop, and maintain Quicksight dashboards, providing leadership with detailed insights and identifying business growth opportunities.
• Engineer data models and improve infrastructure to ensure we are querying efficiently
• Stay ahead of industry trends and technological advancements to continuously improve processes.
• Surface insights from multiple data sources to support complex operational decision making. Execute and/or coordinate critical, advanced analytics initiatives
• Develop solutions that deliver critical data-driven insights and decision metrics proactively and at scale.
Who you are:
• Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in a quantitative or scientific field (Economics, Finance, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Physics, etc.) or equivalent experience
• 4-7+ years of analytical experience in business intelligence or analytics;
• Significant proficiency in SQL. AWS Redshift experience a plus
• Must have expert level experience with standard analysis tools (e.g., Microsoft Excel)
• Experience with business intelligence (BI) and analysis tools (Quicksight, Tableau, Power BI, etc.). Quicksight experience a plus.
• Must possess a demonstrated curiosity to understand the “why” in the data
• Ability to convey technical topics to non-technical audiences
• Excellent communication skills a must
• Ability to understand complicated problems and supply concise and relevant answers
• Engineering experience in AWS Glue a plus
• Ability to work independently in rapidly growing environment, handling multiple competing priorities with excellent attention to detail and organizational skills

item.title: Data Analyst using SQL, Google Sheets, Tableau and Power BI - Upwork
item.description:
Who we are looking for
We need a skilled analyst to help us build out both our backend data transformations and end user data reporting.  The ideal candidate will have the capacity to understand what the data represents in the real world, it’s organizational context, and how end users can use the data.  They will then be able to map that back to the data visualizations, data transformations, and database structures needed to support end users.  It’s the difference between writing a query after someone has told you exactly what that query should do and being able figure out what the query should do based on the end product we are striving for.

We also need someone capable to writing clear documentation to allow others to understand what you have built.

What the job is like
Day to day, this will involve building and maintaining tables, views, and stored procedures in a SQL database.  Designing and building visualizations in Power BI, including DAX formulas and Power Query transformations.  Designing and building in Crystal Reports.  We don’t expect you to be an expert in all of the tools that we use, but we want you to be experienced with some of them and capable of learning others.  This is a remote position.

Primary Qualifications (need to have)
• SQL (Intermediate to Advanced)
• Power BI Development (Intermediate to Advanced)
• DAX (Intermediate to Advanced)
• Deep understanding of Relational Databases

Secondary Qualifications (nice to have)
• Crystal Reports Development (Intermediate to Advanced)
• Microsoft Access (Intermediate to Advanced)
• Python (a Plus)
• Intermediate Excel User
• Power Query
• SQL database management

Who we are looking for
We need a skilled analyst to help us build out both our backend data transformations and end user data reporting.  The ideal candidate will have the capacity to understand what the data represents in the real world, it’s organizational context, and how end users can use the data.  They will then be able to map that back to the data visualizations, data transformations, and database structures needed to support end users.  It’s the difference between writing a query after someone has told you exactly what that query should do and being able figure out what the query should do based on the end product we are striving for.

We also need someone capable to writing clear documentation to allow others to understand what you have built.

Day to day, this will involve building and maintaining tables, views, and stored procedures in a SQL database.  Designing and building visualizations in Power BI, including DAX formulas and Power Query transformations.  Designing and building in Crystal Reports.  We don’t expect you to be an expert in all of the tools that we use, but we want you to be experienced with some of them and capable of learning others.  This is a remote position.

item.title: E-commerce Reporting and Analytical Rep - Upwork
item.description:
Job Title: Reporting and Analytical Specialist
Company: Guardian Baseball
Guardian Baseball is a rapidly growing direct-to-consumer brand specializing in baseball equipment. Leveraging platforms such as Shopify, Amazon, Walmart.com, and more, we are committed to providing high-quality products and exceptional customer service to baseball enthusiasts nationwide.
Position Overview:
We are seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Reporting and Analytical Specialist to join our dynamic team. In this role, you will be responsible for extracting data from various sources, compiling comprehensive reports, generating analytical charts, and conducting insightful sales analyses. The ideal candidate will have a strong analytical mindset, exceptional attention to detail, and the ability to deliver actionable insights that drive business decisions.
Key Responsibilities:
• Extract and analyze data from multiple platforms including Shopify, Amazon, Walmart.com, and other relevant e-commerce channels.
• Compile detailed reports on sales performance, customer behavior, marketing campaigns, and other key metrics.
• Develop and maintain automated dashboards and reporting tools to monitor KPIs and business performance.
• Create visualizations and analytical charts to present findings in a clear and concise manner.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including Marketing, Sales, and Operations to provide data-driven insights and recommendations.
• Identify trends and opportunities for optimization to improve business efficiency and profitability.
• Proactively identify data discrepancies or issues and provide solutions to ensure data accuracy and integrity.
• Stay updated on industry trends and best practices in e-commerce analytics and reporting.
Qualifications:
• 3+ years of experience in a similar role, preferably within e-commerce or consumer goods industry.
• Proficiency in data extraction and manipulation using SQL, Excel, and/or other data analysis tools.
• Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets and translate insights into actionable recommendations.
• Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Google Data Studio.
• Excellent communication skills with the ability to present findings clearly and effectively to stakeholders.
• Proven track record of working independently, managing multiple priorities, and meeting deadlines.
Why Join Us:
• Opportunity to work with a passionate team in a fast-growing industry.
• Remote work flexibility with a results-driven environment.
• Room for growth and professional development within a thriving company.
If you are a self-motivated individual with a passion for data analysis and a desire to make an impact in e-commerce, we encourage you to apply for our Reporting and Analytical Specialist position at Guardian Baseball. Help us drive success through data-driven insights and join us in shaping the future of our brand.

seeking an expert to develop a comprehensive and automated Excel file for managing and monitoring rental properties for students. The primary functions of this Excel file should include:

Input Sheet: A dedicated sheet for entering all relevant data, such as tenant information, rental rates, and lease dates.

Cash Flow Timeline: A sheet that automatically generates a timeline of cash flow, illustrating when tenants move in and out, and projecting monthly income.

Expense Tracking: A sheet for recording and tracking all incurred costs, ensuring a detailed overview of expenditures.

Automation and Enhancement: The entire file needs to be fully automated and significantly enhanced in both functionality and appearance compared to the basic version we currently use.

I will provide an initial Excel file that I created, which serves as a rudimentary version of what we need. The goal is to transform this into a polished, professional tool with advanced automation and comprehensive features.

item.title: Mathematical Modeler and Data Visualization Expert - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a highly skilled Mathematical Modeler and Data Visualization Expert to join our team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in running mathematical models and visualizing the results for complex data sets. As a Mathematical Modeler, you will be responsible for developing and implementing mathematical models to analyze and solve real-world problems. Additionally, you will collaborate with cross-functional teams to interpret and visualize the results in a clear and concise manner.

    Responsibilities:
    - Run mathematical models to analyze complex data sets
    - Develop and implement mathematical models to solve real-world problems
    - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to interpret and visualize the results

    Requirements:
    - Strong background in mathematical modeling
    - Proficiency in data visualization tools (such as Tableau, Power BI, or D3.js)
    - Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills

item.title: Tableau Data Visualization Expert - Upwork
item.description:
We are seeking a skilled Tableau expert to assist with data visualization projects. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in data visualization and a deep understanding of Tableau. As a Tableau Data Visualization Expert, you will be responsible for creating interactive and visually appealing dashboards, reports, and presentations using Tableau. You will work closely with our team to identify data requirements and develop effective visualization solutions that communicate complex data in a clear and concise manner.

    Responsibilities:
    - Collaborate with stakeholders to understand data visualization needs
    - Design and develop Tableau dashboards, reports, and presentations
    - Perform data analysis and identify trends, patterns, and insights
    - Optimize existing visualizations for enhanced user experience
    - Ensure data accuracy and integrity in visualizations

    Requirements:
    - Proven experience in data visualization using Tableau
    - Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
    - Proficiency in data manipulation and analysis tools
    - Excellent communication and collaboration skills

    If you are a Tableau expert with a passion for turning complex data into meaningful insights, we would love to hear from you. This is a fantastic opportunity to work on exciting projects and showcase your data visualization skills.

Budget: $1,500

Category: Data Visualization
